eaking through Neriak Commons =-<br>
<br>
Once you zone into Neriak make sure you hit the sneak/hide buttons immediately.  If you are spotted before you do, or if someone has see invis, move immediately down the wall to the right.  Once you reach the corner near the stalagmite/stalagtite sit tight and listen for words of warning over /shout and /ooc.  You are safe here from any possible experience loss unless someone trains a guard to you and removes your sneak/hide.<br>
<br>
Nobody saw you? Great. Even if they had.. now's the time to act. If you move up the rock column you will be really close to the top of the wall.  If you still have a SOW you can leave S/H on and make a &quot;running&quot; jump to get to the top of the wall.  If you no longer have SOW you will have to unhide and then run and jump.  As soon as you are on the top of the wall immediately S/H again.  Note: There is a slim possibility that a roaming guard will be nearby and see you, but if you are fast enough with your hotkeys you can probably hide without him noticing you.  The roamer walks the path between the small tunnel into Ogretown and the main entrance of Neriak.<br>
<br>
You can go two ways now.  You can begin to sneak over to the regular zone into Neriak Commons or move toward the secret tunnel in Ogretown.  What secret tunnel?  Oh my, you're going to love this.  First, the regular zone.  Sneak along the walls and move into the tunnel that leads into Neriak Commons.  You're pretty safe inside that tunnel from any guards.  Evils are your biggest threat now.  Once you zone into Commons from the tunnel you will be above a pool of water.  There is a waterfall to the right after you move into the Commons a bit.  Unhide at this point and run/jump into the waterfall, aiming up.  You will burst through the waterfall and now be inside a small secret tunnel that runs through the Neriak Commons.<br>
<br>
Sneaking into the tunnel via Ogretown can be risky, but is generally an area that is not travelled that much.  From the wall you jumped on move straight ahead along the right wall.  You will move through a small tunnel and then down a ramp to the left.  There is a big neon symbol near where your destination is.  Sneak toward it and instead of going through it follow the walkway directly across from it.  Enter the first building on your right.  Once inside move through the first door on the left.  Straight ahead is a wall marked with red runes.  That's an illusionary wall that enters into a tunnel.  For light races; it's extremely dark in here.  You should be able to see the outlines of the walls but have a lightstone ready for your first time in.  The tunnel isn't very long and is a rather safe area to rest/camp etc.  At the end is the zone into the Neriak Commons portion of the tunnel.<br>
<br>
-= The Tunnel Network =-<br>
<br>
As I mentioned earlier the waterfall is one way to enter the tunnel from Neriak Commons.  The other is the zone I just mentioned from the Foreign Quarter.  The tunnel is rather simple.  After some exploring you will be able to find a few nooks and crannies that you can hide behind if anyone happens to be searching for you (I once hid here for around 2 real time hours while a hunting party searched for me).  Here's a good chance for you to take advantage of safe fall too.  After the zone in from the Foreign Quarter you can either go right or left through the tunnel.  To the right the tunnel ends but there is a hidden pit trap before the end of the tunnel.  Falling down the pit places you in a small cavern just off the tunnel.  It too has an illusionary wall leading out to the tunnel right near the waterfall.  If you are ever being chased through the tunnels be sure to stop right before the pit trap and let your adversary follow you down.. they will take an unhealthy chunk of damage from the drop.<br>
<br>
The tunnel continues down a ramp at the waterfall.  There are a few twists and turns but it is generally a straight run from the waterfall to the other end.  At the end of the tunnel are a set of stairs that lead up into the Toadstool Inn in Neriak Commons.<br>
<br>
